"Last month we discussed the nature of incident management and contrasted the pro-active management approach with the older, more common reactive response approach. It will always be true, unfortunately, that we will have to respond on occasion – something always gets past the best of defenses and preparations. But our objectives are to create a pro-active environment where we have as few incidents as possible, the ones we have are of significantly lower severity, and we have more time to respond in a controlled, effective manner. This month we will apply our approach to a mock incident and see how it works in practice."
